5000|$|John F. Kennedy {{used the}} phrase in his 1961 inaugural address, when he {{described}} the U.S. and the Soviet Union, [...] "both racing to alter that uncertain <b>balance</b> <b>of</b> <b>terror</b> that stays the hand of mankind's final war".|$|E
